Sixteen killed in Pakistani rainstorms . At least 16 people were killed by lightning and rainstorms in Pakistan - ruled Kashmir overnight , state police said on Tuesday . They said eight people were killed by lightning in a village northeast of the state capital Muzaffarabad and another eight were swept away by flash floods caused by heavy rains in the area . Widespread rains over the past few days have also flooded low - lying areas in Pakistan ' s central province of Punjab , government officials said . 
